The article is a transcript of remarks made by Acting President Hwang Kyo-ahn of South Korea and Vice President Mike Pence of the United States during a joint press conference. Hwang welcomed Pence on his first visit to Korea and emphasized the strong alliance between the two countries in the face of North Korea's nuclear and missile threats. They discussed the need for cooperation in security, economy, and trade, and the importance of China's role in pressuring North Korea. Pence reaffirmed the United States' commitment to South Korea's safety and security and warned North Korea not to test President Trump's resolve. He also called on China to address the North Korean threat and expressed confidence that they would do so, but emphasized that the US and its allies would take action if necessary. Pence highlighted the enduring bond between the US and South Korea, forged through shared sacrifice and values.